APSH
====

APSH stands for "Active Portable Shell". My goal is to create a C++ based shell that uses built
in funtions/commands (like RW and filesystem commands) instead of using preinstalled binaries.
This makes the shell portable for any computer, without the need of proper utilities or dependency
issues. Additionally, you could run a command that lets you use your own binaries that were pre
installed with your distribution. Here are some of the dependencies you need for compiling APSH:

- Git

- BASH

- GNU Compiler Collection (gcc)

- GCC's C++ compiler (g++)


Right now, APSH is only avalible for POSIX systems, including:

- Linux distributions (Debian, Gentoo, etc)

- BSD distributions (FreeBSD, OpenBSD, NetBSD)

- UNIX distributions (They are somewhat dead, but APSH is compatible with them.)

- MacOS systems (MacOS is NetBSD based.)
